The paper deals with a combinatorial optimization problem on planar graphs, which suggests that it could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. The problem involves finding paths in a graph, which could also fall under Computational Geometry (cs.CG) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The use of reduction from Vertex Cover indicates that Complexity Theory (cs.CC) could also be a relevant category. Finally, the paper involves analyzing the structure of the graph, which could be related to Graph Theory (cs.GT).
